@whizzy no, some people don't "happen to naturally be omnivores". We are all humans, the same species. We have molars, and our jaws are able to move side to side to graze on plants, which carnivores such as dogs, and cats don't have and can only move their jaw up and down.
And just because we have 4 canine teeth doesn't mean we are obliged to eat meat. Horses, primates, hippos, some deer and more have canine teeth, but are herbivores/frugivores.
Gorillas, chimpanzees, orangutans and other primates who are genetically close to us are mainly herbivores/frugivores, other than eating some insects sometimes.
